## Functional Requirements

### Inputs

The tool accepts the following runtime inputs, provided via command-line arguments or a configuration object:

| Parameter | Description |
|---|---|
| `env` | Deployment environment (e.g., `dev`, `prod`) |
| `title` | Game title identifier (e.g., `hgt`, `rdr2`) |
| `subject` | Kafka subject prefix (env is appended at runtime) |
| `schemaFile` | Filename of the XML config (must be in same directory as executable) |
| `registryUrl` | URL of the Confluent Schema Registry |
| `updateRegistry` | Boolean flag; if true, schemas are pushed to registry. If false, dry-run only. |

The XML config file follows the `LeaderboardsConfiguration` schema, containing `StatGroups`, `Inputs`, `Categories`, and `CategoryPermutations` sections.

### Outputs

- One Avro schema (JSON) is generated per `StatGroup` found in the XML.
- All schemas are written to a single local file: `{subject}_avro_schema.json`.
- If `updateRegistry` is true, each schema is registered to the Schema Registry under the subject: `{subject}-{statGroupName}-value`.
- Console output is produced at each major step for observability.

### Dry Run Mode

When `updateRegistry` is false, the tool builds and writes schemas locally but does not call the Schema Registry. This is the default safe mode.

