### Interfaces

#### `IXmlParser`

Responsible for reading the XML config file and converting it into a structured `Dictionary<string, object>` representation, equivalent to the Python `convert_xml_to_dict` / `convert_xml_to_json` logic.

```csharp
public interface IXmlParser
{
    Dictionary<string, object> ParseFile(string filePath);
    Dictionary<string, object> ParseString(string xmlContent);
}
```

---

#### `ITypeMapper`

Maps SQL/primitive type strings to their corresponding Avro type representation. Handles upcasting (e.g., float → double) and logical types (e.g., datetime → timestamp-millis).

```csharp
public interface ITypeMapper
{
    object GetAvroTypeForSqlType(string sqlType);
}
```

Returns either a `string` (e.g., `"string"`, `"int"`) or a `Dictionary<string, string>` for logical types (e.g., `{ "type": "long", "logicalType": "timestamp-millis" }`).

---

#### `IAvroSchemaBuilder`

Core interface responsible for transforming the parsed XML dictionary into a list of Avro schema records — one per stat group.

```csharp
public interface IAvroSchemaBuilder
{
    List<Dictionary<string, object>> BuildAvroSchema(Dictionary<string, object> jsonData);
}
```

Internally this orchestrates:
- `GetBaseFieldSchema()` — builds the fixed base fields (handle, tag, time, guid, accountId, etc.)
- `BuildCategories()` — resolves `CategoryPermutations` into Avro record fields
- `BuildInputsAndAggregatedInputs()` — resolves `Columns` into input, aggregatedInputs, and aggregatedValues Avro record fields
- `ProcessStatGroup()` — assembles a full Avro record for one stat group
- `BuildComplexStatFields()` — resolves a single field by name from the Inputs/Categories data, with ratio fallback logic

These are internal methods on `AvroSchemaBuilder` and do not need to be exposed on the interface.

---

#### `ISchemaRegistrar`

Handles registration of compiled Avro schemas to the Schema Registry. Calls existing Schema Registry API clients in the codebase — no new HTTP logic is written here.

```csharp
public interface ISchemaRegistrar
{
    Task RegisterAsync(string subjectName, string avroSchemaJson);
    void PrintSchema(string subjectName, string avroSchemaJson);
}
```

---

#### `IBootstrapperApp`

Top-level orchestrator interface. Wires together parsing, building, file writing, and registration.

```csharp
public interface IBootstrapperApp
{
    Task RunAsync();
}
```

The concrete `BootstrapperApp` takes all other interfaces via constructor injection (DI-friendly).

---

### Dependency Injection

All interfaces are registered in `Program.cs` using .NET 8.0's built-in DI:

```csharp
var host = Host.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
    .ConfigureServices((ctx, services) =>
    {
        services.Configure<BootstrapperOptions>(ctx.Configuration);
        services.AddSingleton<ITypeMapper, TypeMapper>();
        services.AddSingleton<IXmlParser, XmlParser>();
        services.AddSingleton<IAvroSchemaBuilder, AvroSchemaBuilder>();
        services.AddSingleton<ISchemaRegistrar, SchemaRegistrar>();
        services.AddSingleton<IBootstrapperApp, BootstrapperApp>();
    })
    .Build();

await host.Services.GetRequiredService<IBootstrapperApp>().RunAsync();
```

